			<p><img src="images\Turtle.jpg" alt="Turtle" style="float:left"><h1>Turtle</h1>
			To turn op over and gain side control.</br>
			Ops in turtle, you are at their side, hand cupping far shoulder/tricep, arm pit into waist/back, knee into hole between elbow and knee.
			With right arm over op, left hand goes under their chin for the far wrist, right arm moves from shoulder to go around their butt and grab the far ankle or foot,
			slide off the back abit so shoulders and chin are controlling the back, then pull arms towards yourself as in a row and push with shoulders/head to turn op over.
			You end up in side control, get you knee in to touch their belt, keep their knee and elbow apart.
			</p>
